Nun ja. Ich war leider im Vergleich zu anderen Steakhäusern in Kapstadt nicht begeistert gewesen. Begann schon damit, dass der Kellner wenig Interesse zeigte, das Essen bzw. die Karte zu erläutern bzw. auch eine Empfehlung zu geben, Essen und/oder Getränke betreffend. Da fehlte für ein Restaurant dieser gehobenen Kategorie sämtliche Motivation dem Gast gegenüber. Ambiente modern, angenehm, aber teils, aufgrund der Anzahl der Gäste im Restaurant, einfach teils sehr laut (ebenso die Musik), und es roch, vermutlich von der Lüftung herkommend, teils nach Rauch im Restaurant.
Qualität meines Essens, nun ja, Fleisch okay, Chips eher geschmacklich schwach, Salat schmeckte nicht frisch. Der Tisch wurde dann mit meiner benutzten Serviette kurz gereingt zwischendurch  (NO GO!!). Manager ließ sich am Tisch einmal bei der Vorspeise blicken, danach nicht wieder. Einen Vorschlag des Kellners auf ein Dessert, man kann es erraten, wurde gar nicht erst hingewiesen seitens des Personals. Ich bin nun seit 6 Tagen in Kapstadt, habe einige Steakhäuser und Ketten durchprobiert bisher, kann aber sagen: NV-80 Grill&Bar ist preislich intensiv für Südafrika aber qualitativ eher enttäuschend. Freue mich morgen wieder auf den Hussar Grill Mouille Point. Von meiner Seite aus für das NV-80 keine Weiterempfehlung. Ich werde es meiden.

reviews_data.review_text:
Quick Takeaways

🍽️ Excellent food — perfectly cooked meat, fish, and sides

👨‍🍳 High service standards — friendly, professional, attentive staff

🏙️ Convenient location — upstairs in a shopping complex near hotels

💰 Fair pricing for portion size and quality

🪑 Seating a little uncomfortable — wooden chairs could use padding

🧽 Over-eager clearing — staff a bit too quick to remove dishes mid-meal

🌃 Safe area — well lit with visible security and police presence

👌 Refined interior design — elegant, dark, and modern atmosphere

Full Review

Had a lovely meal here. From walking in to walking out, the service and standards were spot on.

The restaurant sits on the first floor of a shopping complex, just off the main road. Parking isn’t great, but there is some on-road parking immediately outside, and car parks nearby. If you’re staying in one of the local hotels, it’s an easy and safe walk, with well-lit streets and a strong security presence in the area.

Inside, the interior is high-end and refined, with a dark, elegant design that gives a clear sense of quality and prestige.

The staff were superb — polite, friendly, knowledgeable, and genuinely keen to ensure everything was just right. Their professionalism and attention to detail really stood out.

The food was delicious and beautifully presented. Both the red meats and fish were cooked perfectly, and the side dishes complemented them perfectly. I couldn’t fault a single element of the meal.

From a price perspective, it was fair value for the portion sizes and quality delivered.

The only negatives were minor: the wooden chairs are quite hard, so a bit of padding would go a long way comfort-wise. And while the staff were excellent overall, the constant attempts to clear plates, glasses, and cutlery mid-meal were a bit distracting. It’s better practice to wait until the table is ready or the customer indicates so — having arms reaching across while you’re still eating breaks the flow of an otherwise relaxed dining experience.

That said, this seems to be a common practice across many restaurants in the region, so I won’t let it affect the overall score.

A great restaurant, with quality food, strong service, and a refined atmosphere — definitely worth a visit. 👏

Visited in December 2024.
South Africa. Capetown.
Seeking a seafood-centric dining experience, we discovered NV80. The restaurant itself is beautifully appointed, a spacious and airy venue with ample seating, decorated in a bright and welcoming palette.

The Food:

The menu is extensive, showcasing a strong focus on both seafood and grilled meats. We opted for a selection of appetizers and individual main courses. The Vietnamese-style oysters were a triumph – plump, fresh, and the perfect start to our meal. Next, the baby calamari were truly exceptional; tender and delicate, their slightly spicy tomato sauce was expertly balanced, resulting in a melt-in-your-mouth experience rarely achieved with this ingredient.

In contrast, the Wagyu burger felt somewhat underwhelming in comparison to the seafood dishes. Ordered medium, it arrived closer to well-done, leaving the patty dry and lacking sufficient sauce and seasoning. The overall flavor profile was rather bland; a few adjustments would significantly elevate this dish. The grilled langoustines, however, were outstanding. Perfectly cooked, they were succulent and tender, and the garlic butter accompaniment was the ideal complement.

Service:

Service was impeccable. As the only diners present, we enjoyed undivided attention; the service was prompt, friendly, and the food arrived swiftly.

In conclusion:

NV80 exceeded our expectations. The ambiance, the high quality of the food, and the attentive service combine to create a truly delightful dining experience. This restaurant is highly recommended for its delicious food and welcoming atmosphere. A perfect combination!

reviews_data.review_text:
I haven't been to NV-80 during my last stays in Cape Town and thought it's time to refresh my memories.
I knew, that the atmosphere was not as stylish or cozy as other restaurants in Cape Town, but this time it felt like sitting in a station hall. With that high ceilings and no partitions it's getting really noisy and loud, even if its only half full. I would highly recommend to work on the atmosphere, as you really feel where this restaurant is located: Inside a shopping mall!

After a warm welcome by the manager we got our table. Unfortunately our choice, the Springbok, was not available (since a long time, as the waiter said). But that could happen. So we decides to go fir the Calamari tubes with some garlic bun as a starter and for the Main we had the fillet with Risotto and Cream Spinach. The food was absolutely perfect: Calamari had a nice flavor and the meat was such a good quality and on point done. The Cream Spinach also one of the best I had here in Cape Town. We were not expecting too much from the Risotto and to be honest, the Risotto was just cooked rice with some veggies and cheese on top. If you know what a Risotto can be you wouldn't call this Risotto. But as I said, we didn't expect too much!
For dessert we had a nice Chocolate Fondant with Armagnac Ice Cream, also worth trying.

Let's talk about the wine list...
I was really disappointed by the selection of wines they do offer. About three different wines per variety is not what you expect when having dinner in a place like this in Cape Town, where the best wineries are minutes away. We decided to try the Rijk Touch of Oak Shiraz, which was a bit like a lottery, cause the wine list just says Rick Shiraz. If you know a bot about wine you would expect a bit more information (Which range is the wine from? Which vintage is the wine from?....). And that is not a information only a Sommelier can work with, it is necessary as the different ranges of the wineries do have different qualities, prices and aromas. The information Rijk Shiraz or Creation Pinot Noir includes more than one wine of this wineries!!!
The wine itself was nice and slightly chille, which I highly appreciate in this climate. Sometimes reds are served way to warm. But the wine glasses..... How can you pour a red wine in a small glass, which is maximum the size of a white wine glass (if its was that big)? to enjoy a good wine the glass needs to match with the wine. You don't need variety glasses but there is a difference between red and white wine glasses. You might also use a red wine glass for a white, but not the other way?

Service in genreal was okay. Not what you get sometimes here in Cape Town, but not bad. We've missed a bit of a personality. But it matched with the whole atmosphere.
At the end we were surprised, that tables around us got some free Dom Pedros before paying, while we didn't... But that was just a small issue.

We were wondering, that the manager, who was very attentive in the beginning, wasn't been seen after 10 pm. When we left the restaurant, we saw him sitting at the table, right next to the entrance/exit, having his dinner... It is absolutely understandable that each and everyone should have his break and meal, but how can it be, that there is only one manager on duty (Hussar Grill Camps Bay always got a minimum of two) who is not present for an hour, having his meal in the middle of a still operating restaurant?
Hospitality is really good in Cape Town, service standards are high. Please have a look at other restaurants with the standard you wanna provide and work on those little things, to be a part of that league.

I am trained in service industry and also wine, working in that business since more than 20 years, so I think I can evaluate the standard and quality of the offered service.

- Food 5*
- Atmosphere 2*
- Service 3*
- Wine 3*

Although NV-80 is situated in a mall, none of our guests are exposed to the external outlets once they've been seated inside our venue. The first thing you encounter when you enter is the Sanitizer-Spray Bottle and then the host will take each patrons temperature, show that they comply to and with COVID-Management as per government regulations, directing your attention to this fact where each guest must scan the Bar-Code into their cell-phone and fill out their details as this is administered by “dineplan”. After as this is behind your back you can choose your seating. It was rather sad to note that all the Wines were in jail as in locked-up behind steel mashed netting gates. The beautiful large impressive bar where the Draught-Taps stood like ornaments because they were bone-dry more like Drought-Taps! But didn’t dampen our spirits as they still had sparkling-water and juices to toast with. The restaurant floor-space is massive they even have loads of tables with seating on the “L” shaped outside balcony with the one section direct-lii under the “Lions Head” peak which today was awesome-lii surrounded by a cloud. The decor is neat the wall at the bar is filled with some nice paintings and above the bar counter they have two wire-boats. The manager on floor-duty was very polite and friend-lii and so was our waitron. There is much to choose from on the menu. As they serve you fresh brown-bread with a nice pungent strong dip before you order we decided to skip the starter and go straight to the mains. My wife is a carnivore and ordered a 300g rump-steak and a side of chips. The rest of us were hook by the Calamari-Tubes in a light garlic-marinade and chips. The steak looked more like 500g and filled the plate it was excellent-lii done just as ordered and tender. The calamari was succulent and well flavoured they even threw in same baby-squid which added a niff-tii twist to the presentation and it was indeed delicious. The desert menu is short they list only 3 kinds to choose from 1. Chocolate Fondant / Armagnac-ice cream, 2. Creme Brulee / vanilla, hazelnut shortbread 3. Baked Cheesecake / white chocolate ganache. Seen that we had a birthday-girl here we requested that they serve us all three dessert on one platter and scribble “Happy Birthday” on the plate with chocolate lettering which the manager glad-lii obliged to and even glad-lii serve the dessert-platter and sang “happy birthday” to the birthday-girl, how cool and how awesome was that extra-act which only strengthens and solidifies of repute for the exquisite restaurant. They serve nice cappuccinos but the cups are way too small! We high-lii recommend this venue for any celebration
